-- Extend membership lifecycle: add CALON state for prospective members.
DO $$
BEGIN
  ALTER TYPE "StatusNasabah" ADD VALUE IF NOT EXISTS 'CALON';
EXCEPTION
  WHEN duplicate_object THEN NULL;
END $$;

-- New nasabah records now start as CALON.
ALTER TABLE "nasabah"
  ALTER COLUMN "status" SET DEFAULT 'CALON';

-- Support tenant-scoped status filtering for lifecycle dashboards/queries.
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS "nasabah_companyId_status_idx"
  ON "nasabah"("companyId", "status");
---
# Phase 1 Membership Schema Design

## Lifecycle Status Update (2026-04-23)

`StatusNasabah` now includes `CALON` to represent prospective members before activation.

### Prisma Changes

- Enum `StatusNasabah` values: `CALON`, `AKTIF`, `NON_AKTIF`, `KELUAR`.
- `nasabah.status` default changed from `AKTIF` to `CALON`.
- Added index `@@index([companyId, status])` on `Nasabah` for tenant-scoped lifecycle filtering.

### Migration Notes

Migration: `prisma/migrations/20260423130500_nasabah_status_calon/migration.sql`

- Adds enum value `CALON` (`ALTER TYPE ... ADD VALUE IF NOT EXISTS`).
- Updates DB default for `nasabah.status` to `CALON`.
- Adds DB index `nasabah_companyId_status_idx` on `("companyId", "status")`.

### Seed Compatibility Notes

- Current seed scripts do not explicitly set `nasabah.status`, so any future seeded `nasabah` records will default to `CALON`.
- If a seed scenario requires active members immediately, set `status: "AKTIF"` explicitly on create.

